  <div class="main content-container" role="main">
    
      <div class="article-teaser">
        We have worked with the London boroughs and other stakeholders through the sub-regional partnerships to develop an integrated approach to sub-regional transport planning and analysis.
        
      </div>
    
    <div class="on-this-page">
      <p>The sub-regional transport programme includes regular meetings, the development of Sub-regional transport plans, and ongoing work on local and strategic transport assessment and infrastructure planning.</p>
<p>The plans were first developed in 2010 and updated several times since then&nbsp;through sub-regional partnerships led by TfL Planning.</p>
<p>The 2016 update - called 'Story of Growth' - includes greater analysis of transport conditions and forecast travel patterns, economic conditions and infrastructure provision. The plans are more interactive and more detailed&nbsp;and are intended to provide the basis for future planning, transport and investment decisions between the relevant authorities.</p>
<p>See the documents on the <a href="/corporate/publications-and-reports/sub-regional-transport-plans">Sub-regional transport plans page in Publications</a>.
</p>
<p>The documents will help boroughs develop their latest complementary <a href="/info-for/boroughs/local-implementation-plans">Local Implementation Plan (LIP)
programmes</a>.</p>
<p>For more information on the Sub-regional plans,&nbsp;email&nbsp;<a href="mailto:BoroughPlanning&#64;tfl.gov.uk">BoroughPlanning&#64;tfl.gov.uk</a>.</p>
      
           
      
      
        
          
